				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Gamma $$\end{document} valley and the HH band according to each specified generation rate with a Gaussian spectral profile centered around the beam excitation energy. The optical transition probabilities between the subbands are proportional to the oscillator strength due to wavefunction overlap. Recombination (radiative, traps, etc.) is simulated by random selection of electron–hole pairs to be removed from the Γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
