The fast electron–electron interaction allows the electrons to thermalize to a Fermi–Dirac distribution on a time scale around 0.1 ps, and these electrons lose energy to phonons with a similar time constant. Although CW excitation keeps adding newly generated electrons to the system, our EMC results suggest the majority of the electrons still have close to Fermi–Dirac distributions during most of the simulation period. This allows us to estimate the electron temperature Te\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
